854 A.2d 876 ATTORNEY GRIEVANCE COMMISSION OF MARYLAND, Petitioner, v. Joel CHASNOFF, Respondent. Misc. AG No. 2,

Sept. Term, 2004.

Court of Appeals of Maryland. July 22, 2004.

ORDER

RAKER, J.

Upon consideration of the Joint Petition for Disbarment by Consent filed herein pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-772, it is this 22nd day of July, 2004,

ORDERED, by the Court of Appeals of Maryland, that Joel Chasnoff, be, and he is hereby, disbarred by consent from the further practice of law in the State of Maryland; and it is further,

ORDERED, that the Clerk of this Court shall strike the name of Joel Chasnoff from the register of attorneys, and pursuant to Maryland Rule 16-772(d), shall certify that fact to the Trustees of the Client Protection Fund and the clerks of all judicial tribunals in the State.
